<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-05T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="540" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/776:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-05T19:00:00-04:00">September 5, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>202. Your 221, September 4, 1 p.m. Confirmation has been received
                                from the Treasury of the payment of $87,168 on the Greek debt. The
                                Department is highly gratified at the outcome of your conversations
                                with the Premier and commends you for the successful manner in which
                                you have handled this matter.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>